Instruction: Using metric_window (filtered metric rows inside Mar 9 13:00–13:30 UTC+8) and metric_summary (global p95_value per cmdb_id/kpi_name), find consecutive anomaly runs for the following components: IG01, Tomcat01, Tomcat02, Tomcat03, Tomcat04. Define an anomaly point as value >= group's global p95_value. For each cmdb_id and kpi_name, detect all consecutive runs of anomaly points and output a compact table (limit 20 rows) with columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, run_start_timestamp, run_end_timestamp, run_length (number of consecutive points), max_value_in_run, severity_ratio = max_value_in_run / p95_value, count_points_in_window (from metric_window), p95_value, median_value. Order results by run_length desc then severity_ratio desc. Also save the full runs table to a kernel variable named faults_table for later steps. Only include runs with run_length >= 2 (to filter isolated spikes).
